# Atlas OS — Environment Configuration

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values. **Never commit `.env` or real API keys.**

```powershell
copy .env.example .env
```

## Required for Atlas workspace (Docker on Windows)

```env
ATLAS_WORKSPACE_HOST=C:\AtlasWorkspace
ATLAS_WORKSPACE_CONTAINER=/workspace
```

## LLM providers (optional — configure at least one)

```env
# OpenAI (optional)
OPENAI_API_KEY=
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-5.5

# Local Ollama on the Docker host (optional)
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434
```

## Desktop Bridge (optional — Windows host)

```env
ATLAS_BRIDGE_TOKEN=change-this-token
DESKTOP_COMMANDS_ENABLED=false
```

## Web UI bind (defaults are safe for local use)

```env
APP_BIND=127.0.0.1
APP_PORT=7000
AUTH_ENABLED=true
```

## Search & vector store (Docker Compose overrides in-network URLs)

```env
SEARXNG_INSTANCE=http://localhost:8080
```

## Additional deployment overrides

See commented sections in the repository for ChromaDB, embeddings, GPU compose overlays, auth, and cleanup intervals. The Docker stack reads most service URLs from `docker-compose.yml`; only override when you know you need to.

**Security:** Keep `.env` local. Rotate any key that appears in logs, screenshots, or shared chats.
